/target
**/*.rs.bk
*.swp
.DS_Store

# Local mounts and runtime data
/runtime
/mnt
*.db
*.db-shm
*.db-wal

# Editor
.vscode/
.idea/

# Secrets — .env holds API tokens (Teamwork Graph, etc.). NEVER commit.
# The committed reference is .env.example; it lists variable NAMES only.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Playwright MCP scratch output
.playwright-mcp/

# MkDocs build output
/site

# Python cache (from scripts/*.py)
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Recordings
*.cast
demo/recording.gif

# Local research scratch (committed manually)
research/scratch/

# Claude Code session artifacts (ephemeral; re-created on each run).
# We list specific subpaths instead of ignoring `.claude/` wholesale so
# that project-level skills under `.claude/skills/` and agent definitions
# under `.claude/agents/` remain committed — OP-4 (self-improving
# infrastructure) requires them to ship in lockstep with the code/doctrine
# they encode (doctrine-institutionalization Stage B, session 7e2a4cf2).
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/worktrees/
.claude/conversations/
.claude/sessions/
.claude/cache/
.claude/logs/

# Byproducts of scripts/bench_token_economy.py not involving fixtures:
runtime/bench-*.log
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock

# SESSION-END-STATE per-run logs (regenerated on every `verify`). Artifacts
# under .planning/verifications/<category>/ ARE tracked — only the verifier
# stdout/stderr captures are runtime noise.
.planning/verifications/_logs/

# docs-build/animation-renders (quality/catalogs/docs-build.json) is a
# catalog-first row whose verifier script + artifact are intentionally absent
# until the owner uploads the mp4 (see the row's owner_hint). Every
# `quality/runners/run.py` invocation hits the "verifier not found" branch
# (~L272-294) and rewrites this exact path with a
# {"error": "verifier not found..."} stub — untracked cruft, not committed
# evidence, unlike its sibling playwright/*.json artifacts (real graded
# results) which ARE tracked. Exact path only — do not broaden to a glob;
# other .planning/verifications/playwright/**/*.json artifacts stay tracked.
.planning/verifications/playwright/index/animation.json

# Quality Gates runtime artifacts (per-run; regenerate on every runner invocation).
# .gitkeep placeholders under verifications/ + verdicts/ ARE tracked so the
# directory tree exists in git; only the per-row JSON + per-run timestamped
# verdict files are runtime noise. Canonical VERDICT.md and named evidence
# artifacts (honesty-spot-check.md, triage.md, verifier-prompt.md, etc.)
# per phase ARE tracked. The pattern below matches only timestamped runtime
# snapshots — files whose name starts with a digit (e.g.
# 2026-04-30T09-07-50Z.md). Renamed pattern from the broader *.md +
# !VERDICT.md exception to avoid accidentally untracking named evidence
# (caught in PR #31 cleanup; see commit 4b6f8f3 reversal).
quality/reports/verifications/*/*.json
# kcov shell-coverage Codecov artifact (per-run; regenerated by
# quality/gates/code/shell-coverage.sh, uploaded by the CI shell-coverage job).
quality/reports/verifications/*/*.cobertura.xml
# p94-git243-fallback-sentinel.sh archives the full cargo-test log here on
# failure (post-mortem diagnostics) — per-run runtime snapshot, not evidence.
quality/reports/verifications/agent-ux/p94-git243-fallback-sentinel-cargo-test-failure.log
# P124 DRAIN-14: container-rehearse.sh writes a per-run ephemeral-sim stdout/stderr log
# at quality/reports/verifications/docs-repro/.sim-<row-id>.log (SIM_LOG) for each rehearsal.
# It is transient runtime noise (regenerated on every run), never committed evidence —
# previously it leaked as untracked. Scoped to the docs-repro dir (NOT a repo-wide *.sim
# glob), mirroring the p94 sentinel-log precedent above.
quality/reports/verifications/docs-repro/.sim-*.log
# Exception: P84 webhook-latency.json is `asset-exists`-kind committed
# evidence — the verifier `webhook-latency-floor.sh` READS this artifact
# on every pre-release run; it's not a per-run runtime snapshot.
!quality/reports/verifications/perf/webhook-latency.json
# P93 cache-coherence verifier outputs (p93-*.json): per-run verification artifacts —
# their catalog rows in quality/catalogs/agent-ux.json carry these paths as `artifact`
# OUTPUT destinations, regenerated on every gate run. v0.13.0 milestone-close force-tracked
# and NEGATED them here (`!...p93-*.json`) to dodge a release-plz "tracked-AND-ignored →
# uncommitted changes" abort. v0.14.0 P111 milestone-close reclassified them as ephemeral
# and untracked them (`git rm --cached`); the broad `*/*.json` rule above now (correctly)
# ignores them, so they are untracked-AND-ignored — invisible to release-plz, which resolves
# the original blocker WITHOUT the fragile force-negation. The committed load-bearing PASS
# record is quality/reports/verdicts/p93/VERDICT.md; the JSONs stay on disk, regenerable by
# re-running the p93-*.sh gates. (Removing the 5 `!` exceptions IS the P111 root-cause fix.)
quality/reports/verdicts/*/[0-9]*.md
# kind: shell-subprocess transcripts (RBF-FW-02) are per-run runtime snapshots,
# same as verifications/*.json above — the dir is scaffolded by .gitkeep and the
# convention is documented in quality/catalogs/README.md; regenerate any
# transcript by running its verifier (e.g. quality/gates/agent-ux/shell-subprocess-example.sh).
quality/reports/transcripts/*.txt
quality/reports/verdicts/session-end/SESSION-VERDICT.md
quality/reports/badge.json
# P123 SC3 (DRAIN-05): the advisory persist-lock file
# (quality/runners/_persist_guard.py::catalog_persist_lock) — a zero-payload
# OS-level flock target used only to serialize concurrent `--persist` runners.
# Pure runtime coordination state, never evidence; the kernel releases the flock
# on process exit so a stale file is harmless.
quality/reports/.persist.lock
